{
  "cleanUrls": true,
  "rewrites": [
    { "source": "/", "destination": "/gdn-ai-trial.html" },
    { "source": "/app", "destination": "/gdn-ai-portal.html" },
    { "source": "/invest", "destination": "/gideon.html" }
  ],
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/",
      "headers": [
        { "key": "Cache-Control", "value": "no-store, max-age=0" },
        { "key": "CDN-Cache-Control", "value": "no-store" },
        { "key": "Vercel-CDN-Cache-Control", "value": "no-store" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "/(.*\\.html)",
      "headers": [
        { "key": "Cache-Control", "value": "no-store, max-age=0" },
        { "key": "CDN-Cache-Control", "value": "no-store" },
        { "key": "Vercel-CDN-Cache-Control", "value": "no-store" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
Commit. Vercel redeploys in ~1 minute and gdn-ai.com/invest goes live.
Even simpler alternative (no JSON): rename your local copy of the page to invest.html and upload it the same way you just did. Because the site has clean URLs on, invest.html automatically becomes gdn-ai.com/invest — no vercel.json change needed. (Slight downside: two copies of the page in the repo.)

Either one works. Once you've done it, say the word and I'll confirm gdn-ai.com/invest is live and that the link-preview card unfurls correctly.

One reminder for when you're ready to share widely: the Register form won't email gnardo@gdngroup.com.au until the Resend key is added in Vercel — worth doing first so the leads actually reach you.



